                <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Ti</abbr><ex>berius</ex></expan> Claudius</supplied> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">C</supplied>aesar A<supplied reason="lost">ugus</supplied>tus <lb n="3"/>Germanicu<supplied reason="lost">s</supplied> <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>pont</abbr><ex>ifex</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>max</abbr><ex>imus</ex></expan></supplied> <expan><abbr>tr</abbr><ex>ibunicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> VII <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr><supplied reason="lost">i</supplied>mp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> XIIII co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ul</ex></expan> IIII <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ater</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>atriae</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="6"/><supplied reason="lost">ce</supplied>nsor <lb n="7"/>XXXXVI
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Höhenangabe bezieht sich nur auf den heute sichtbaren Teil; der übrige Teil steckt in der Erde. Bei der Auffindung waren noch mehr Buchstaben erkennbar: Z. 2: Augustus; Z. 3: Germanicus; Z. 4: [pon]t(ifex) max(imus); Z. 5: p(atriae); Z. 6: censor.</p>
            </div>
